"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">47</A>
The cancellation of debts was one of the chief features of Solon's reorganization of the government of Athens in the sixth century <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> The popular term means "shaking off burdens." This incident is discussed by Aristotle, <I>Constitution of Athens</I>, chap. vi, where Solon's innocence of wrongdoing is maintained.


