onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>On Praising Oneself</I>, 541<SPAN CLASS="small">D</SPAN></A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Onomademus" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Praecepta_gerendae_reipublicae*.html#ref:Onomademus
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">e</A>
The story is repeated in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/De_capienda*.html#ref49
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><I>Moralia</I>, 91<SPAN CLASS="small">F</SPAN></A>, where the man's name is better given as Demus. "Onomademus" is what the Loeb translator has here, corresponding to the facing Greek, <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">Ὀνομάδημος.</SPAN> The Loeb edition at 91<SPAN CLASS="small">F</SPAN> prints the Greek as <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">ὄνομα Δῆμος</SPAN>, "by the name of Demus". The readings differ by the accentuation and a space, neither of which is usually marked in manuscripts: the peculiar and unlikely "Onomademus" is an error by a post-Antique editor.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Timoleon_and_the_Good_Daemon" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Praecepta_gerendae_reipublicae*.html#ref:Timoleon_and_the_Good_Daemon
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">f</A>
Also in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Timoleon*.html#36.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><I>Life of Timoleon</I>, chap. xxxvi.6 (253<SPAN CLASS="small">D</SPAN>)
	</A>
and
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/De_se_ipsum_laudando*.html#Timoleon_and_the_Good_Daemon
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>On Praising Oneself</I>, 542<SPAN CLASS="small">E</SPAN></A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Python_quote" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Praecepta_gerendae_reipublicae*.html#ref:Python_quote
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">g</A>
Also in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/De_se_ipsum_laudando*.html#Timoleon_and_the_Good_Daemon
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>On Praising Oneself</I>, 542<SPAN CLASS="small">F</SPAN></A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Theopompus_on_obedience" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Praecepta_gerendae_reipublicae*.html#ref:Theopompus_on_obedience
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">h</A>
Also in Plutarch's collection of sound-bites by Theopompus
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Sayings_of_Spartans*/main.html#Theopompus.4
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(<I>Sayings of Spartans</I>, 221<SPAN CLASS="small">E</SPAN>)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:maxim_of_Jason_of_Pherae" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Praecepta_gerendae_reipublicae*.html#ref:maxim_of_Jason_of_Pherae
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">i</A>
Also in
	<A HREF="
